WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:23.000
Bathsheba the Witch by Jane Elizabeth Kamak copyright black cat publishing

00:23.000 --> 00:35.000
Witches When we think of witches, we usually think of old women with black hair, black clothes and a black hat.

00:35.000 --> 00:41.000
They are usually very ugly and laugh when they do something bad.

00:41.000 --> 00:47.000
Witches say strange words like hocus pocus.

00:47.000 --> 00:54.000
At Halloween children often dress like witches to try to scare their friends.

00:54.000 --> 01:04.000
Witches are a popular subject of stories, both old and modern stories and especially children's stories.

01:04.000 --> 01:08.000
Do you know the sisters who are witches in the Wizard of Oz?

01:08.000 --> 01:12.000
One is the wicked witch of the east.

01:12.000 --> 01:19.000
She is the leader of the munchkin people and she wears magical silver shoes.

01:19.000 --> 01:24.000
With these shoes she can transport anyone anywhere they wish to go.

01:24.000 --> 01:29.000
Her sister is the wicked witch of the west.

01:29.000 --> 01:32.000
She is the leader of the winky people.

01:32.000 --> 01:39.000
She has got green skin and a big nose and she always wears black clothes.

01:39.000 --> 01:44.000
She lives in a castle with her pets, the winged monkeys.

01:44.000 --> 01:52.000
The people are afraid of her but she is afraid of the dark.

01:52.000 --> 01:59.000
Chapter 1 The House in the Forest

01:59.000 --> 02:07.000
In the middle of a dark forest on the top of a high mountain there is a black house.

02:07.000 --> 02:17.000
The garden gate is black, the flowers in the garden are black and the front door is black too.

02:17.000 --> 02:21.000
A witch lives in this house.

02:21.000 --> 02:25.000
Witches in stories are usually bad.

02:25.000 --> 02:30.000
They have got big noses and long black hair.

02:30.000 --> 02:34.000
They make terrible potions and spells.

02:34.000 --> 02:42.000
They go out at night on their broomsticks and their clothes are always black.

02:42.000 --> 02:48.000
But this witch, the witch in this story, is different.

02:48.000 --> 02:55.000
Her name is Bathsheba and she is a good and beautiful witch.

02:55.000 --> 03:02.000
Her hair is curly and blonde and she has got a small nose.

03:02.000 --> 03:07.000
She buys her fashionable clothes from magazines.

03:07.000 --> 03:14.000
Bathsheba lives alone in the black house with her white cat, cobweb.

03:14.000 --> 03:17.000
She has got a very important job.

03:17.000 --> 03:22.000
Bathsheba is a weather witch.

03:22.000 --> 03:30.000
Down in the valley just below the dark forest there is a pretty village called Sunnyville.

03:30.000 --> 03:34.000
In Sunnyville the weather is always good.

03:34.000 --> 03:40.000
In summer the sky is blue and it is never too hot.

03:40.000 --> 03:46.000
In autumn the red and orange leaves fly into the next village.

03:46.000 --> 03:51.000
In winter icicles hang from the trees.

03:51.000 --> 03:59.000
Ice covers the roofs in December and on Christmas day the snow always falls.

03:59.000 --> 04:05.000
When spring arrives the new flowers grow fast in the good weather.

04:05.000 --> 04:14.000
It doesn't rain in Sunnyville, well only at night and every day it is sunny.

04:14.000 --> 04:18.000
No one in the village knows about the witch.

04:18.000 --> 04:28.000
No one knows that Bathsheba on her new turbo broom paints the dark clouds white and makes the grey sky blue.

04:28.000 --> 04:35.000
Bathsheba the witch pushes the storm clouds into the next valley.

04:35.000 --> 04:40.000
Bathsheba and cobweb have got a very difficult job.

04:40.000 --> 04:43.000
Sometimes they work all night.

04:43.000 --> 04:51.000
They change the weather for the next day and when morning comes they are very tired.

04:51.000 --> 04:56.000
They go back to the black house for breakfast.

04:56.000 --> 05:07.000
Everything is sunny in Sunnyville until one day.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
The weather in Great Britain.

05:10.000 --> 05:15.000
In Britain the weather changes very often.

05:15.000 --> 05:25.000
It can be sunny one day and rainy the next and so it is difficult to know what the weather is going to be like.

05:25.000 --> 05:31.000
In the story Bathsheba changes the weather with her turbo broom.

05:31.000 --> 05:38.000
Now let's look at some things which really change the weather in Great Britain.

05:38.000 --> 05:41.000
The wind.

05:41.000 --> 05:49.000
Different parts of Britain have different weather because the winds come from different directions.

05:49.000 --> 05:54.000
The origin of the wind influences the weather in Britain.

05:54.000 --> 06:00.000
In the north a very cold wind blows from the Arctic.

06:00.000 --> 06:05.000
In the east the winds are cold and dry.

06:05.000 --> 06:15.000
These winds come from the continents of Europe and Asia and we call them continental winds.

06:15.000 --> 06:20.000
In the south the winds can be warm and tropical.

06:20.000 --> 06:25.000
They come from the area near the equator, the tropics.

06:25.000 --> 06:29.000
In the west they are warm and wet.

06:29.000 --> 06:38.000
This is because the wind crosses the Atlantic Ocean and brings clouds and rain.

06:38.000 --> 06:41.000
The Gulf Stream.

06:41.000 --> 06:45.000
The sea is very important in Britain.

06:45.000 --> 06:53.000
Britain is a small island and the sea around it also influences the weather.

06:53.000 --> 07:06.000
The ocean near Mexico and the Caribbean is warm and a current of this warm water comes across the Atlantic Ocean to the west coast of Britain.

07:06.000 --> 07:17.000
This is called the Gulf Stream and it can increase the temperature of the air by 5 to 8 degrees Celsius.

07:17.000 --> 07:20.000
The seasons.

07:20.000 --> 07:23.000
Britain has a temperate climate.

07:23.000 --> 07:29.000
This means that it is usually warm and it often rains.

07:29.000 --> 07:38.000
There are four seasons in Britain, spring, summer, autumn and winter.

07:38.000 --> 07:49.000
The typical weather is different in each season but there isn't usually any extreme weather because of the influence of the sea.

07:49.000 --> 07:54.000
In winter it is often cold, wet and windy.

07:54.000 --> 08:02.000
Sometimes it can snow but the temperature doesn't usually go below not degrees Celsius.

08:02.000 --> 08:12.000
In summer it can be hot but temperatures are usually about 26 degrees Celsius.

08:12.000 --> 08:15.000
Differences in the regions.

08:15.000 --> 08:22.000
There are some big differences in the weather between the different regions of Britain.

08:22.000 --> 08:29.000
On the west coast of Britain the weather is usually warm and wet.

08:29.000 --> 08:37.000
This is because of the wind, the Gulf Stream and because some of the land is high.

08:37.000 --> 08:45.000
In the east of Britain however the land is low and the weather is usually dry.

08:45.000 --> 08:53.000
The average temperatures in the north of England and Scotland are different from those in the south of England.

08:53.000 --> 09:06.000
The average high temperature in London in July is 22 degrees Celsius but in Glasgow it is 19 degrees Celsius.

09:06.000 --> 09:09.000
Hours of daylight.

09:09.000 --> 09:15.000
The number of hours of daylight also changes with the season and the region.

09:15.000 --> 09:21.000
The latitude influences the number of hours of daylight in a country.

09:21.000 --> 09:32.000
London is at 51 degrees north latitude and Loewick in the north of Scotland is at 60 degrees north.

09:33.000 --> 09:43.000
In December in London there are 7 hours 50 minutes of daylight and in Loewick there are 5 hours 50 minutes.

09:43.000 --> 09:49.000
In summer the number of hours of daylight is very different.

09:49.000 --> 10:01.000
In June in London there are 16 hours and 40 minutes of daylight and in Loewick there are 18 hours and 50 minutes.

10:02.000 --> 10:10.000
Chapter 2 The Invisible Potion

10:10.000 --> 10:15.000
One summer day a wind arrives from the east.

10:15.000 --> 10:22.000
It is a warm wind, a wind that plays in the gardens, a wind of change.

10:22.000 --> 10:27.000
Bathsheba wakes up early and she feels different.

10:27.000 --> 10:30.000
I want to go down to the village.

10:30.000 --> 10:32.000
She says to cobweb.

10:32.000 --> 10:37.000
Cobweb looks at her with his big green eyes.

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
It's dangerous I know.

10:39.000 --> 10:41.000
She continues.

10:41.000 --> 10:44.000
Because humans don't like witches.

10:44.000 --> 10:48.000
Cobweb size and closes his eyes.

10:48.000 --> 10:51.000
Bathsheba drinks her tea.

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
I know.

10:53.000 --> 11:00.000
She says I can make a spell, my invisible spell.

11:00.000 --> 11:04.000
So Bathsheba finds her spell book.

11:04.000 --> 11:12.000
She puts some rain, a white cloud and two spoons of fog into her cauldron.

11:12.000 --> 11:21.000
Then she adds some invisible powder and stirs the potion with a big wooden spoon.

11:21.000 --> 11:24.000
Two spoons the spell says.

11:24.000 --> 11:29.000
And Bathsheba drinks the green potion.

11:29.000 --> 11:32.000
She feels very different.

11:32.000 --> 11:35.000
Bathsheba looks in the mirror.

11:35.000 --> 11:38.000
There is no one there.

11:38.000 --> 11:41.000
Cobweb opens one eye.

11:41.000 --> 11:45.000
He feels a light wind crossing the room.

11:45.000 --> 11:49.000
The door opens and closes.

11:49.000 --> 11:54.000
He sighs and then eats his breakfast.

11:54.000 --> 11:57.000
Bathsheba is free.

11:57.000 --> 12:02.000
She runs across a meadow near the stream and through the forest.

12:02.000 --> 12:07.000
She jumps over stones and under branches.

12:07.000 --> 12:11.000
She goes down the mountain and into the village.

12:11.000 --> 12:18.000
She dreams so often of this world where the humans live and now she is there.

12:18.000 --> 12:24.000
In the middle of the village there is an area of grass called the green.

12:24.000 --> 12:31.000
Around the green there are shops, a cafe and lots of small cottages.

12:31.000 --> 12:35.000
There is a pub called the green dragon.

12:35.000 --> 12:37.000
How strange!

12:37.000 --> 12:39.000
Bathsheba thinks.

12:39.000 --> 12:43.000
That the villagers know about the green dragon.

12:43.000 --> 12:45.000
There is a pond.

12:45.000 --> 12:51.000
There are ducks swimming in the pond and there are benches where people can sit.

12:51.000 --> 12:53.000
It's beautiful.

12:53.000 --> 12:55.000
Bathsheba says.

12:55.000 --> 13:00.000
She wants to know more about the people who live here.

13:00.000 --> 13:03.000
Bathsheba goes into the butchers.

13:03.000 --> 13:07.000
Here they sell steaks and other meat.

13:07.000 --> 13:15.000
And Mr Jones, the butcher, has got a kind red face and a big nose.

13:15.000 --> 13:20.000
He is wearing a white apron and a butcher's hat.

13:20.000 --> 13:25.000
Bathsheba doesn't like meat so she goes next door.

13:25.000 --> 13:29.000
The next shop is the bakers.

13:29.000 --> 13:35.000
There are lots of different kinds of bread and hundreds of delicious cakes.

13:35.000 --> 13:38.000
My invisible spell is fun.

13:38.000 --> 13:40.000
Thanks Bathsheba.

13:40.000 --> 13:42.000
And she takes a cake.

13:42.000 --> 13:49.000
Mr Smith, the baker, can see a cream cake flying out of the shop.

13:49.000 --> 13:53.000
Then Bathsheba goes into the green grocers.

13:53.000 --> 13:56.000
There are lots of people in the shop.

13:56.000 --> 14:04.000
There are old ladies with bags of fruit, children with apples and there is a soldier.

14:04.000 --> 14:11.000
He is wearing a beautiful red jacket, black trousers and black boots.

14:11.000 --> 14:16.000
He has got dark brown hair and light grey eyes.

14:16.000 --> 14:20.000
He is very handsome.

14:20.000 --> 14:22.000
Goodbye Mr Cherry.

14:22.000 --> 14:26.000
Captain Troy says and he leaves the shop.

14:26.000 --> 14:29.000
He has got a lovely voice.

14:30.000 --> 14:33.000
Bathsheba is in love.

14:37.000 --> 14:42.000
Chapter three, a witch in love.

14:42.000 --> 14:45.000
His name is Captain Troy.

14:45.000 --> 14:48.000
Bathsheba tells Cobweb.

14:48.000 --> 14:52.000
He's got a red jacket and black boots.

14:52.000 --> 14:54.000
He's very handsome.

14:54.000 --> 14:58.000
Cobweb puts his paws over his ears.

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
Don't you understand Cobweb?

15:00.000 --> 15:02.000
I'm in love.

15:02.000 --> 15:04.000
Says Bathsheba.

15:04.000 --> 15:08.000
She dances around the kitchen with her broomstick.

15:08.000 --> 15:11.000
Then she sits down and says.

15:11.000 --> 15:14.000
But I'm a witch.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.000
And he's a soldier.

15:16.000 --> 15:19.000
He can't be my boyfriend.

15:19.000 --> 15:23.000
Bathsheba cries all day.

15:23.000 --> 15:31.000
She can't eat and when evening comes her eyes are red and she is very tired.

15:31.000 --> 15:33.000
She goes to sleep.

15:33.000 --> 15:40.000
At midnight her alarm clock rings but Bathsheba sleeps and sleeps.

15:40.000 --> 15:44.000
There is thunder and lightning in the sky.

15:44.000 --> 15:46.000
She doesn't hear it.

15:46.000 --> 15:51.000
Cobweb tries to wake her up but it is not possible.

15:51.000 --> 15:56.000
At 8am the morning sky is grey, not blue.

15:56.000 --> 16:01.000
The rain falls but Bathsheba is asleep.

16:01.000 --> 16:05.000
All the people in the village come out of their houses.

16:05.000 --> 16:08.000
They look at the sky.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
It's not possible.

16:10.000 --> 16:13.000
Says Mr Jones the butcher.

16:13.000 --> 16:16.000
It never rains during the day.

16:16.000 --> 16:18.000
Thunder!

16:18.000 --> 16:20.000
How strange!

16:20.000 --> 16:23.000
Says Mr Smith the baker.

16:23.000 --> 16:26.000
The sky is always blue.

16:26.000 --> 16:29.000
Where's the song today?

16:29.000 --> 16:31.000
Mr Cherry says.

16:31.000 --> 16:35.000
Sunnyville is famous for its good weather.

16:35.000 --> 16:42.000
Every year when all the villages enter the good weather competition we always win.

16:42.000 --> 16:45.000
Because our village has the best weather.

16:45.000 --> 16:48.000
This is a disaster.

16:48.000 --> 16:53.000
And they have a meeting about the problem in the pub.

16:53.000 --> 16:57.000
At midday Bathsheba wakes up.

16:57.000 --> 17:00.000
She looks at the grey sky.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
She sees the rain.

17:02.000 --> 17:05.000
Then she looks at her watch.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.000
Twelve o'clock.

17:07.000 --> 17:09.000
She says.

17:09.000 --> 17:12.000
Oh no!

17:12.000 --> 17:16.000
And she starts to cry again.

17:16.000 --> 17:21.000
I love a soldier and I can't do my job.

17:21.000 --> 17:24.000
She says to cobweb.

17:24.000 --> 17:28.000
Weather wizard only likes witches who work.

17:28.000 --> 17:32.000
Witches who don't work get terrible jobs.

17:32.000 --> 17:35.000
They have to look after wizards children.

17:35.000 --> 17:38.000
And you know how terrible they can be.

17:38.000 --> 17:41.000
Then the telephone rings.

17:41.000 --> 17:44.000
Bathsheba is afraid.

17:44.000 --> 17:46.000
Seven four nine three.

17:46.000 --> 17:48.000
She says quietly.

17:48.000 --> 17:51.000
Can I speak to the weather witch please?

17:51.000 --> 17:53.000
A happy voice says.

17:53.000 --> 17:54.000
Speaking.

17:54.000 --> 17:56.000
This is Dr Miracle.

17:56.000 --> 17:57.000
He says.

17:57.000 --> 18:00.000
And I can make miracles.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
What kind of miracles?

18:02.000 --> 18:04.000
Bathsheba asks.

18:04.000 --> 18:06.000
A lot of different kinds.

18:06.000 --> 18:10.000
But weather problems are my speciality.

18:10.000 --> 18:11.000
Really?

18:11.000 --> 18:13.000
Well I've got lots of problems.

18:13.000 --> 18:15.000
Bathsheba says.

18:15.000 --> 18:16.000
Can you help me?

18:16.000 --> 18:17.000
Certainly.

18:17.000 --> 18:18.000
He says.

18:18.000 --> 18:21.000
See you this afternoon at two p.m.

18:21.000 --> 18:23.000
Goodbye.

18:27.000 --> 18:30.000
Listening activity.

18:30.000 --> 18:34.000
The fair weather competition.

18:34.000 --> 18:38.000
Is the weather in your village always good?

18:38.000 --> 18:42.000
In summer is the sky always blue?

18:42.000 --> 18:45.000
Does it snow on Christmas day?

18:45.000 --> 18:51.000
If the answer is yes enter the fair weather competition.

18:51.000 --> 18:56.000
The competition is on the 21st of June at two p.m.

18:56.000 --> 19:01.000
in the town hall in the center of Oxford.

19:01.000 --> 19:06.000
To enter the competition bring four photographs of your village.

19:06.000 --> 19:08.000
One of each season.

19:08.000 --> 19:11.000
And we can choose a winner.

19:11.000 --> 19:15.000
The first prize is five hundred pounds for your village

19:15.000 --> 19:20.000
and the chance to see your photographs in the local paper.

19:20.000 --> 19:33.000
Phone the tourist office on 01802 659 874 for more information.

19:33.000 --> 19:35.000
Chapter 4.

19:35.000 --> 19:39.000
Marvelous Dr Miracle.

19:39.000 --> 19:44.000
At two o'clock a limousine arrives at the black house.

19:44.000 --> 19:47.000
Dr Miracle is a large man.

19:47.000 --> 19:53.000
He has got a round pink face and a long moustache.

19:53.000 --> 19:58.000
He is wearing a long dark cloak over his brown suit.

19:58.000 --> 20:04.000
He has got a yellow waistcoat and his shoes are long and striped.

20:04.000 --> 20:09.000
In his hand he is carrying a large red bag.

20:09.000 --> 20:12.000
So you're the village's weather witch?

20:12.000 --> 20:13.000
He says.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.000
Where's your computer?

20:15.000 --> 20:16.000
I haven't got one.

20:16.000 --> 20:18.000
Bathsheba says.

20:18.000 --> 20:23.000
I use this turbo broom to push the dark clouds away.

20:23.000 --> 20:25.000
Here is my paint.

20:25.000 --> 20:29.000
Blue for the sky and white for the clouds.

20:29.000 --> 20:35.000
I use my magic spells and so the rain falls only at night.

20:35.000 --> 20:39.000
Dr Miracle looks at her and smiles.

20:39.000 --> 20:41.000
You work very hard.

20:41.000 --> 20:43.000
He says.

20:43.000 --> 20:47.000
Young weather witches use technology to help them.

20:47.000 --> 20:49.000
So you need this.

20:49.000 --> 20:53.000
He takes a small white computer out of his bag.

20:53.000 --> 20:57.000
This weather computer does everything.

20:57.000 --> 20:59.000
He explains.

20:59.000 --> 21:04.000
When he turns it on there are a lot of colors on the screen.

21:04.000 --> 21:09.000
Bathsheba can see a bright green light under the keyboard.

21:09.000 --> 21:13.000
Every evening you can program the weather.

21:13.000 --> 21:15.000
Then the computer does the work.

21:15.000 --> 21:17.000
Says Dr Miracle.

21:17.000 --> 21:21.000
It moves the dark clouds and paints the sky.

21:21.000 --> 21:26.000
Marvelous Dr Miracle shows her how to do it.

21:26.000 --> 21:31.000
Bathsheba is a clever witch and she soon understands.

21:31.000 --> 21:35.000
The computer is a fantastic invention.

21:35.000 --> 21:36.000
He says.

21:36.000 --> 21:38.000
And so you can go out.

21:38.000 --> 21:40.000
You can go down to the village.

21:40.000 --> 21:42.000
You can go dancing.

21:42.000 --> 21:47.000
When he says this, Bathsheba starts to cry.

21:47.000 --> 21:49.000
What's the matter?

21:49.000 --> 21:51.000
asks Dr Miracle.

21:51.000 --> 21:53.000
I love Captain Troy.

21:53.000 --> 21:58.000
I want to go down to the village but I can't.

21:58.000 --> 21:59.000
She says.

21:59.000 --> 22:01.000
Why not?

22:01.000 --> 22:04.000
Dr Miracle asks in a kind voice.

22:04.000 --> 22:08.000
Because humans don't like witches.

22:08.000 --> 22:11.000
Bathsheba replies.

22:11.000 --> 22:14.000
Dr Miracle laughs.

22:14.000 --> 22:20.000
Only bad witches and only witches in stories.

22:21.000 --> 22:25.000
You need one of my special love potions.

22:25.000 --> 22:29.000
Dr Miracle opens his cloak.

22:29.000 --> 22:36.000
Inside there are lots of little pockets and in every pocket there are some bottles.

22:36.000 --> 22:44.000
There are small bottles, round bottles and square bottles in every color.

22:44.000 --> 22:49.000
He gives her a small bottle with a pink potion in it.

22:49.000 --> 22:52.000
He'll spray once near his nose.

22:52.000 --> 22:54.000
Says Dr Miracle.

22:54.000 --> 22:56.000
That's all you have to do.

22:56.000 --> 22:58.000
Good luck.

22:58.000 --> 23:03.000
Dr Miracle gives her his email address and leaves.

23:03.000 --> 23:06.000
Bathsheba looks at the small bottle.

23:06.000 --> 23:09.000
Then she runs upstairs.

23:09.000 --> 23:13.000
She must choose the right clothes to wear.

23:13.000 --> 23:16.000
Cobweb comes into the bedroom.

23:16.000 --> 23:21.000
The wardrobe doors are open and clothes fly over his head.

23:21.000 --> 23:25.000
A pair of jeans falls onto the bed.

23:25.000 --> 23:28.000
There is a white blouse on the bedside table.

23:28.000 --> 23:32.000
A pink skirt is next to the lamp.

23:32.000 --> 23:36.000
There are eight pairs of shoes on the floor.

23:36.000 --> 23:38.000
How do I look?

23:38.000 --> 23:41.000
Bathsheba finally says.

23:41.000 --> 23:45.000
Cobweb looks at her from under the bed.

23:45.000 --> 23:52.000
Cobweb is wearing white leggings, a white skirt and a pink and grey t-shirt.

23:52.000 --> 23:55.000
She looks lovely.

23:55.000 --> 23:59.000
She puts the love potion in her bag and goes out.

23:59.000 --> 24:03.000
Cobweb says goodbye from the front door.

24:03.000 --> 24:07.000
Then he sees Bathsheba's glasses on the table.

24:07.000 --> 24:12.000
She can't see very well without her glasses.

24:12.000 --> 24:18.000
Down in the village, the sun is shining and the villagers are happy again.

24:18.000 --> 24:23.000
People are sitting at tables outside the cafe drinking tea.

24:23.000 --> 24:27.000
And when they see Bathsheba, they are surprised.

24:27.000 --> 24:30.000
They want to know who she is.

24:30.000 --> 24:32.000
Good afternoon.

24:32.000 --> 24:33.000
Bathsheba says.

24:33.000 --> 24:36.000
She is a little afraid.

24:36.000 --> 24:39.000
Do they know that she is a witch?

24:39.000 --> 24:41.000
You're new to the village?

24:41.000 --> 24:44.000
Says Mrs. Dale, the florist.

24:44.000 --> 24:45.000
I'm just visiting.

24:45.000 --> 24:47.000
Says Bathsheba.

24:47.000 --> 24:51.000
And then she sees a red jacket.

24:51.000 --> 24:53.000
It is him.

24:53.000 --> 25:00.000
She is sure that it is Captain Troy.

25:00.000 --> 25:03.000
Potions.

25:03.000 --> 25:08.000
A potion is a medicine which has got special powers.

25:08.000 --> 25:12.000
There are lots of different potions in literature.

25:12.000 --> 25:20.000
Sometimes potions in the stories help people and sometimes they hurt people.

25:20.000 --> 25:24.000
Potions to help people.

25:24.000 --> 25:30.000
In C.S. Lewis's The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe,

25:30.000 --> 25:35.000
Lucy receives an important potion as a Christmas present.

25:35.000 --> 25:41.000
This potion can help people if they are ill or if they hurt themselves.

25:41.000 --> 25:47.000
Lucy uses this potion to help her brother.

25:47.000 --> 25:51.000
Potions to change people.

25:51.000 --> 25:59.000
In the strange case of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde, Dr. Jekyll drinks a potion.

25:59.000 --> 26:05.000
His body changes and he becomes the terrible Mr. Hyde.

26:05.000 --> 26:09.000
Roald Dahl often uses potions in his books.

26:09.000 --> 26:16.000
In George's Marvelous Medicine, George makes a special potion for his grandmother.

26:16.000 --> 26:23.000
He wants to change her from an angry grandma into a sweet kind grandma.

26:23.000 --> 26:27.000
Sleeping Potions

26:27.000 --> 26:32.000
In Shakespeare's Romeo and Juliet, Juliet is in love with Romeo,

26:32.000 --> 26:37.000
but her parents want her to marry another man, Paris.

26:37.000 --> 26:42.000
She doesn't want to marry Paris, so she drinks a sleeping potion.

26:42.000 --> 26:47.000
She sleeps very deeply and her parents think she is dead.

26:47.000 --> 26:52.000
Romeo doesn't know about the potion and he thinks she is dead too.

26:52.000 --> 26:58.000
He loves Juliet very much, so he decides to die too.

26:58.000 --> 27:00.000
Love Potions

27:00.000 --> 27:04.000
In A Midsummer Night's Dream by Shakespeare,

27:04.000 --> 27:10.000
Oberon, the king of the fairies, is very angry with his queen, Titania.

27:10.000 --> 27:14.000
He puts some love potion into her eyes when she is asleep,

27:14.000 --> 27:21.000
and puck Oberon's servant changes the head of one of the characters into the head of a donkey.

27:22.000 --> 27:26.000
This is the first person Titania sees when she wakes up,

27:26.000 --> 27:31.000
and she falls in love with a man with a donkey's head.

27:34.000 --> 27:39.000
Chapter 5 Red Jackets

27:39.000 --> 27:41.000
Captain Troy

27:41.000 --> 27:44.000
Bathsheba says very quietly.

27:44.000 --> 27:48.000
She takes the pink potion from her bag.

27:48.000 --> 27:51.000
The red jacket is near the sweet shop.

27:51.000 --> 27:58.000
She is behind him and she sprays just once near his nose.

27:58.000 --> 28:01.000
The red jacket turns.

28:01.000 --> 28:09.000
Bathsheba can see eyes full of love, but they are small, round and dark.

28:09.000 --> 28:16.000
This man has got curly blonde hair and a big fat face.

28:16.000 --> 28:19.000
It isn't Captain Troy.

28:19.000 --> 28:23.000
My darling, you're very beautiful.

28:23.000 --> 28:28.000
The man in the red coat says, and he takes her hand.

28:28.000 --> 28:31.000
Bathsheba takes her hand away.

28:31.000 --> 28:34.000
I'm sorry, she says to the man.

28:34.000 --> 28:37.000
It's all a mistake, a big mistake.

28:37.000 --> 28:39.000
And then she runs.

28:39.000 --> 28:43.000
The man in the red jacket runs too.

28:43.000 --> 28:48.000
Bathsheba races across the green and into the butchers.

28:48.000 --> 28:50.000
Can I help you?

28:50.000 --> 28:53.000
asks Mr Jones, the butcher.

28:53.000 --> 28:57.000
I've got some lovely stakes.

28:57.000 --> 29:00.000
Sir, a man is in love with me.

29:00.000 --> 29:02.000
Says Bathsheba.

29:02.000 --> 29:04.000
Mr Jones smiles.

29:04.000 --> 29:07.000
How wonderful, he says.

29:07.000 --> 29:10.000
But I don't love him.

29:10.000 --> 29:13.000
Bathsheba replies, please help me.

29:13.000 --> 29:16.000
Is there a door at the back of your shop?

29:16.000 --> 29:18.000
There is.

29:18.000 --> 29:23.000
He says, and he opens the door so Bathsheba can run away.

29:23.000 --> 29:27.000
Good luck, my dear.

29:27.000 --> 29:30.000
She is in a road with tall trees.

29:30.000 --> 29:34.000
Without her glasses, she can't see very well.

29:34.000 --> 29:37.000
She decides to turn right.

29:37.000 --> 29:38.000
You.

29:38.000 --> 29:45.000
Our voice says, the man with the small dark eyes has got his arms around her.

29:45.000 --> 29:47.000
My darling, finally.

29:47.000 --> 29:51.000
He says, but Bathsheba is quick.

29:51.000 --> 29:56.000
Her arms are strong from pushing clouds and painting the sky.

29:56.000 --> 29:59.000
She turns around and runs.

29:59.000 --> 30:02.000
She is fast, but the man follows her.

30:02.000 --> 30:05.000
He shouts words of love.

30:05.000 --> 30:10.000
She asks people to stop her, but no one can.

30:10.000 --> 30:16.000
Bathsheba runs in front of the school, through the sports centre, and finally she arrives

30:16.000 --> 30:18.000
at the forest.

30:18.000 --> 30:25.000
It is not far to her home, but suddenly she sees a man in a red jacket come out from behind

30:25.000 --> 30:27.000
a tree.

30:27.000 --> 30:30.000
Bathsheba falls onto the ground.

30:30.000 --> 30:33.000
She can't run anymore.

30:33.000 --> 30:42.000
She can feel strong arms pulling her up, and a soft voice says, are you all right?

30:42.000 --> 30:48.000
Bathsheba looks into kind eyes and a handsome face.

30:48.000 --> 30:52.000
It is Captain Troy.

30:52.000 --> 30:54.000
Yes, I'm fine.

30:54.000 --> 31:01.000
She says with a soft smile, and then she remembers that she can't talk to him now.

31:01.000 --> 31:07.000
She must get home before the man with the small dark eyes arrives.

31:07.000 --> 31:09.000
Are you new to the village?

31:09.000 --> 31:12.000
Captain Troy asks her.

31:12.000 --> 31:14.000
Bathsheba gets up.

31:14.000 --> 31:16.000
Yes, quite new.

31:16.000 --> 31:17.000
She replies.

31:17.000 --> 31:20.000
And now I really must go.

31:20.000 --> 31:23.000
And she walks away from Captain Troy.

31:23.000 --> 31:27.000
But I don't know your name, or where you live.

31:27.000 --> 31:29.000
He says.

31:29.000 --> 31:31.000
My name's Bathsheba.

31:31.000 --> 31:36.000
She says, and she runs away between the trees.

31:36.000 --> 31:40.000
But Bathsheba forgets something.

31:40.000 --> 31:43.000
She leaves her bag on the grass.

31:43.000 --> 31:50.000
Captain Troy finds the bag and the small bottle of pink potion inside it.

31:50.000 --> 31:56.000
He looks at the bottle and sprays the potion near his nose.

31:56.000 --> 32:02.000
What a wonderful smell.

32:02.000 --> 32:06.000
Listening activity.

32:06.000 --> 32:08.000
Hello, John.

32:08.000 --> 32:13.000
I'm a writer, and I'm writing about Helen of Troy and Hercules.

32:13.000 --> 32:17.000
Can I ask you some questions about Helen of Troy first, please?

32:17.000 --> 32:19.000
Yes, of course.

32:19.000 --> 32:21.000
How do you spell Troy?

32:21.000 --> 32:24.000
It's T-R-O-Y.

32:24.000 --> 32:26.000
Thank you.

32:26.000 --> 32:28.000
Why is Helen famous?

32:28.000 --> 32:32.000
She is famous because she is very beautiful.

32:32.000 --> 32:35.000
And she has got a famous father.

32:35.000 --> 32:36.000
Is that right?

32:36.000 --> 32:38.000
Yes, that's right.

32:38.000 --> 32:40.000
He's Zeus.

32:40.000 --> 32:42.000
He's king of the gods.

32:42.000 --> 32:44.000
And is she married?

32:44.000 --> 32:45.000
Yes.

32:45.000 --> 32:47.000
Her husband is called Menelaus.

32:47.000 --> 32:51.000
But Helen meets another man and falls in love with him.

32:51.000 --> 32:52.000
Who does she meet?

32:52.000 --> 32:54.000
She meets Paris.

32:54.000 --> 32:59.000
But then Menelaus' brother is very angry, and the Trojan War starts.

32:59.000 --> 33:01.000
Thank you, John.

33:01.000 --> 33:04.000
Let's talk about Hercules now.

33:04.000 --> 33:05.000
Certainly.

33:05.000 --> 33:08.000
How do you spell Hercules?

33:08.000 --> 33:13.000
It's H-E-R-C-U-L-E-S.

33:13.000 --> 33:15.000
His father is Zeus, too.

33:15.000 --> 33:18.000
And why is Hercules famous?

33:18.000 --> 33:21.000
Because he's very strong.

33:21.000 --> 33:24.000
There are lots of interesting stories about him.

33:24.000 --> 33:26.000
Can you tell me one?

33:26.000 --> 33:30.000
Well, the goddess Hera hates Hercules.

33:30.000 --> 33:34.000
When he is only a baby, she puts two snakes in his bed.

33:34.000 --> 33:35.000
And what happens?

33:35.000 --> 33:39.000
Baby Hercules kills the snakes with one hand.

33:39.000 --> 33:42.000
His mother finds him playing with the dead bodies.

33:42.000 --> 33:47.000
In the pictures, Hercules always wears something.

33:47.000 --> 33:48.000
What is it?

33:48.000 --> 33:49.000
Oh, yes.

33:49.000 --> 33:52.000
He always wears a lion's skin.

33:52.000 --> 33:54.000
Oh, it's a lion's skin.

33:54.000 --> 33:57.000
Well, thank you very much for your help, John.

33:57.000 --> 33:59.000
It's a pleasure.

34:02.000 --> 34:04.000
Chapter 6.

34:04.000 --> 34:07.000
Love Potion

34:07.000 --> 34:10.000
Captain Troy goes home.

34:10.000 --> 34:13.000
Mrs. Daly is in his cottage.

34:13.000 --> 34:17.000
Every afternoon, Mrs. Daly comes to wash his clothes

34:17.000 --> 34:19.000
and clean his house.

34:19.000 --> 34:25.000
She has got a kind face, but her hands are red from all her work.

34:25.000 --> 34:28.000
Good afternoon, Captain Troy.

34:28.000 --> 34:30.000
She says.

34:30.000 --> 34:35.000
Now, Dr. Miracle's potion is very strong.

34:35.000 --> 34:38.000
When Captain Troy comes into the house,

34:38.000 --> 34:42.000
Mrs. Daly looks like Helen of Troy.

34:42.000 --> 34:46.000
Mrs. Daly, you're very beautiful.

34:46.000 --> 34:51.000
And I want to tell you that I'm completely in love with you.

34:51.000 --> 34:53.000
Captain Troy!

34:53.000 --> 34:55.000
Mrs. Daly says.

34:55.000 --> 35:00.000
Mrs. Daly is married and she is very happy.

35:00.000 --> 35:02.000
She has got four children.

35:02.000 --> 35:08.000
She likes Captain Troy, but she is surprised at what he says to her.

35:08.000 --> 35:13.000
He tries to take her hand, but she runs into the kitchen

35:13.000 --> 35:15.000
and takes a plate out of the cupboard.

35:15.000 --> 35:17.000
You're wonderful, Mrs. Daly.

35:17.000 --> 35:19.000
Says Captain Troy.

35:19.000 --> 35:21.000
I want to marry you.

35:21.000 --> 35:24.000
Captain Troy, you're not well.

35:24.000 --> 35:26.000
Have you got a temperature?

35:26.000 --> 35:28.000
Mrs. Daly asks.

35:28.000 --> 35:30.000
It's you, Mrs. Daly.

35:30.000 --> 35:32.000
Captain Troy replies.

35:32.000 --> 35:35.000
My heart is burning with love for you.

35:35.000 --> 35:41.000
Mrs. Daly throws the plate at Captain Troy, but it doesn't hit him.

35:41.000 --> 35:44.000
She runs out of the house.

35:44.000 --> 35:49.000
The vicar and Miss Price are outside with the church magazines.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.000
Is anything the matter?

35:51.000 --> 35:53.000
The vicar calls.

35:53.000 --> 35:55.000
The captain is not well?

35:55.000 --> 35:57.000
Mrs. Daly shouts.

35:57.000 --> 35:59.000
Call the doctor immediately.

35:59.000 --> 36:03.000
And she runs across the road and into the house opposite.

36:03.000 --> 36:06.000
Captain Troy comes out of his house.

36:06.000 --> 36:09.000
I'm in love with Mrs. Daly.

36:09.000 --> 36:11.000
She's very beautiful.

36:11.000 --> 36:16.000
He says, and he gives the bag and the bottle of pink potion to Miss Price.

36:16.000 --> 36:21.000
Miss Price puts the bottle near her nose and smells it.

36:21.000 --> 36:26.000
She feels different, and she looks at the vicar.

36:26.000 --> 36:31.000
The vicar hasn't got any hair, and he has got a big nose.

36:31.000 --> 36:36.000
But now Miss Price thinks he looks like Hercules.

36:36.000 --> 36:40.000
Oh, Vicar, you're very handsome.

36:40.000 --> 36:45.000
She says, and she gives the vicar a kiss.

36:45.000 --> 36:50.000
The wizard watches from a white cloud, and he sighs.

36:50.000 --> 36:56.000
He sees Captain Troy singing love songs outside the house opposite his own.

36:56.000 --> 37:01.000
He sees the vicar sitting in his car with Miss Price on the roof.

37:01.000 --> 37:05.000
And he looks at the grey sky.

37:05.000 --> 37:09.000
It is time to visit Bathsheba.

37:09.000 --> 37:16.000
Chapter 7. A Visitor.

37:16.000 --> 37:19.000
Oh, cobweb.

37:19.000 --> 37:23.000
Bathsheba says, when she gets home to the black house.

37:23.000 --> 37:25.000
What a disaster!

37:25.000 --> 37:28.000
My glasses are here.

37:28.000 --> 37:31.000
And now this ugly man is in love with me.

37:31.000 --> 37:36.000
My handbag is in the village, and the love potion is inside it.

37:36.000 --> 37:39.000
What can I do?

37:39.000 --> 37:44.000
Cobweb moves the curtain with his paw and looks out of the window.

37:44.000 --> 37:51.000
The cat makes a strange noise, and Bathsheba understands why immediately.

37:51.000 --> 37:53.000
He's here!

37:53.000 --> 37:58.000
She says, and she runs to the front door and turns the key.

37:58.000 --> 38:02.000
Too late. The back door is open.

38:02.000 --> 38:03.000
We must hide.

38:03.000 --> 38:05.000
She says to cobweb.

38:05.000 --> 38:07.000
But wait a minute.

38:07.000 --> 38:09.000
Bathsheba thinks.

38:09.000 --> 38:11.000
I'm a witch.

38:11.000 --> 38:13.000
Where's my wand?

38:13.000 --> 38:17.000
She hears the man fall over her broomstick in the next room.

38:17.000 --> 38:19.000
Aha, here it is.

38:19.000 --> 38:23.000
She says, it is under a chair.

38:23.000 --> 38:25.000
The door handle moves.

38:25.000 --> 38:28.000
Bathsheba finds her spell book.

38:28.000 --> 38:32.000
The man in the red jacket comes into the living room.

38:32.000 --> 38:37.000
His face is red like his clothes, and he has got red roses in his hand.

38:37.000 --> 38:39.000
There you are, my love.

38:39.000 --> 38:42.000
He says, come to me.

38:42.000 --> 38:47.000
Cobweb finds the right page, and Bathsheba holds her wand.

38:47.000 --> 38:50.000
And Bathsheba holds her wand and says,

38:50.000 --> 38:54.000
Frogs and bats, don't leave me alone.

38:54.000 --> 38:58.000
Turn this man into stone.

38:58.000 --> 39:02.000
Suddenly they see a white light.

39:02.000 --> 39:06.000
The man in the red jacket is standing quite still.

39:06.000 --> 39:08.000
He is a statue.

39:08.000 --> 39:09.000
Yes!

39:09.000 --> 39:11.000
Bathsheba says.

39:11.000 --> 39:14.000
We can put him outside in the garden.

39:14.000 --> 39:18.000
He can stop the birds from eating my vegetables.

39:18.000 --> 39:22.000
Bathsheba says a voice.

39:22.000 --> 39:27.000
It is a dark voice with a sound like thunder.

39:27.000 --> 39:29.000
Oh no!

39:29.000 --> 39:33.000
Bathsheba says, she looks at cobweb.

39:33.000 --> 39:35.000
It's the wizard.

39:36.000 --> 39:39.000
Chapter 8.

39:39.000 --> 39:41.000
The wizard.

39:41.000 --> 39:45.000
The wizard is sitting at the table in Bathsheba's kitchen.

39:45.000 --> 39:51.000
He is drinking a large cup of hot chocolate and eating some biscuits.

39:51.000 --> 39:53.000
A disaster.

39:53.000 --> 39:55.000
He finally says.

39:55.000 --> 39:58.000
Now I must go to the village.

39:58.000 --> 40:00.000
Can I help you?

40:01.000 --> 40:03.000
Bathsheba offers.

40:03.000 --> 40:06.000
I don't think so.

40:06.000 --> 40:08.000
He replies.

40:08.000 --> 40:10.000
What a disaster.

40:10.000 --> 40:12.000
He repeats.

40:12.000 --> 40:16.000
People falling in love with the wrong person.

40:16.000 --> 40:21.000
A doctor selling potions and weather machines.

40:21.000 --> 40:23.000
Oh dear.

40:23.000 --> 40:27.000
And the wizard puts his head in his hands.

40:28.000 --> 40:31.000
Can everything go back to normal?

40:31.000 --> 40:33.000
Bathsheba asks.

40:33.000 --> 40:39.000
Well, I must make a spell so that everyone forgets.

40:39.000 --> 40:43.000
Then I must take that poor man to his house.

40:43.000 --> 40:48.000
And finally, I must program the weather machine.

40:48.000 --> 40:51.000
Don't you think that technology is a good thing?

40:51.000 --> 40:53.000
Bathsheba asks.

40:53.000 --> 40:59.000
Yes, but you must do the witches and wizards computer course.

40:59.000 --> 41:02.000
Then you can use the computer.

41:02.000 --> 41:04.000
He says.

41:04.000 --> 41:06.000
Can I ask you something?

41:06.000 --> 41:08.000
Bathsheba says.

41:08.000 --> 41:11.000
It's about Captain Troy.

41:11.000 --> 41:15.000
The wizard looks at her and smiles.

41:15.000 --> 41:18.000
I know everything.

41:18.000 --> 41:19.000
He says.

41:19.000 --> 41:22.000
You're a beautiful witch.

41:22.000 --> 41:25.000
You don't need any love potions.

41:25.000 --> 41:27.000
Do you really think so?

41:27.000 --> 41:29.000
Bathsheba asks.

41:29.000 --> 41:30.000
I do.

41:30.000 --> 41:31.000
He says.

41:31.000 --> 41:36.000
But now we must speak about your punishment.

41:36.000 --> 41:38.000
Punishment?

41:38.000 --> 41:39.000
Says Bathsheba.

41:39.000 --> 41:41.000
Oh yes.

41:41.000 --> 41:43.000
Says the wizard.

41:43.000 --> 41:47.000
Sometimes you don't think before you do things.

41:47.000 --> 41:51.000
And that can be very dangerous.

41:51.000 --> 41:58.000
So, I want you to take this letter to the green dragon.

41:58.000 --> 42:01.000
Not the green dragon?

42:01.000 --> 42:04.000
Bathsheba is afraid.

42:04.000 --> 42:08.000
The wizard gives her the letter and leaves her house.

42:08.000 --> 42:13.000
He takes the man in the red jacket to his house.

42:13.000 --> 42:17.000
Once he is in his bed, he is human again.

42:17.000 --> 42:19.000
Not a statue.

42:19.000 --> 42:26.000
The wizard puts his potion that makes people forget in the eyes of all the villagers.

42:26.000 --> 42:32.000
And before he leaves, he puts love powder into every house.

42:32.000 --> 42:38.000
The next morning, when the people wake up, they can't remember anything.

42:38.000 --> 42:42.000
But they all feel very happy.

42:42.000 --> 42:48.000
And Bathsheba...

42:48.000 --> 42:53.000
Chapter 9 The Green Dragon

42:53.000 --> 42:59.000
All the witches know where the green dragon lives, but no one ever goes there.

42:59.000 --> 43:02.000
They are all afraid of dragons.

43:02.000 --> 43:06.000
They breathe fire and eat people.

43:06.000 --> 43:10.000
Young women are dragon's favorite food.

43:10.000 --> 43:17.000
At midnight, Bathsheba flies over the dark forest and the high rocks where the vultures live.

43:17.000 --> 43:26.000
She flies on through the night sky until she arrives at the castle at the top of Lone Mountain.

43:26.000 --> 43:34.000
There is fog around its towers and hot lava spits at her when she crosses the bridge.

43:34.000 --> 43:43.000
There is a large black door at the entrance of the castle, but when she pushes it, the door opens.

43:43.000 --> 43:48.000
Bathsheba walks into the great hall.

43:48.000 --> 43:51.000
It is dark and cold.

43:51.000 --> 43:57.000
She can hear the sound of her feet in the big empty room.

43:57.000 --> 44:00.000
Where is the dragon?

44:00.000 --> 44:03.000
Is anyone home?

44:03.000 --> 44:05.000
She calls.

44:05.000 --> 44:07.000
Excuse me.

44:07.000 --> 44:09.000
She tries again.

44:09.000 --> 44:13.000
I'm looking for the green dragon.

44:13.000 --> 44:18.000
Suddenly, she hears an angry voice coming through the corridors.

44:18.000 --> 44:23.000
It is a very loud voice and Bathsheba is afraid.

44:23.000 --> 44:25.000
Who are you?

44:25.000 --> 44:27.000
It says angrily.

44:27.000 --> 44:32.000
Um, I'm Bathsheba the weather witch.

44:32.000 --> 44:36.000
She says in a very small voice.

44:36.000 --> 44:38.000
Why are you here?

44:38.000 --> 44:41.000
The voice shouts again.

44:41.000 --> 44:44.000
I've got a letter for you from the wizard.

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
She says.

44:46.000 --> 44:57.000
Two light blue eyes shine out from the darkness, and then she sees an emerald green dragon standing in front of her.

44:57.000 --> 44:59.000
A letter?

44:59.000 --> 45:01.000
For me?

45:01.000 --> 45:07.000
He says, and big dragon tears fall onto the floor.

45:07.000 --> 45:10.000
The dragon is crying.

45:10.000 --> 45:13.000
No one comes to see me.

45:13.000 --> 45:20.000
No one brings me letters, and I'm all alone in this castle.

45:20.000 --> 45:22.000
That's terrible.

45:22.000 --> 45:29.000
Says Bathsheba, and she gently puts her hand on the dragon's face.

45:29.000 --> 45:35.000
Everyone is afraid of you, and they don't know what a lovely dragon you are.

45:35.000 --> 45:37.000
What's your real name?

45:37.000 --> 45:39.000
It's Gulliver.

45:39.000 --> 45:44.000
The dragon replies, and he opens the letter.

45:44.000 --> 45:46.000
Oh!

45:46.000 --> 45:49.000
Gulliver reads the letter.

45:49.000 --> 45:51.000
He looks very happy.

45:51.000 --> 45:54.000
Oh, how exciting!

45:54.000 --> 46:00.000
A job from the wizard, and I need the help of an old friend.

46:00.000 --> 46:03.000
But how can I find her?

46:03.000 --> 46:05.000
Send her an email.

46:05.000 --> 46:07.000
Bathsheba suggests.

46:07.000 --> 46:09.000
I can help you.

46:09.000 --> 46:11.000
You're very kind.

46:11.000 --> 46:15.000
He says, and he shows Bathsheba the letter.

46:15.000 --> 46:17.000
She reads it.

46:17.000 --> 46:19.000
How interesting!

46:19.000 --> 46:24.000
Says Bathsheba.

46:24.000 --> 46:28.000
Listening activity.

46:28.000 --> 46:29.000
Excuse me?

46:29.000 --> 46:30.000
Yes?

46:30.000 --> 46:34.000
I don't understand why all these people are in the streets.

46:34.000 --> 46:37.000
Because today is the 23rd of April.

46:37.000 --> 46:39.000
I'm sorry.

46:39.000 --> 46:40.000
I come from Italy.

46:40.000 --> 46:44.000
Is the 23rd of April a special day?

46:44.000 --> 46:46.000
It's St George's Day.

46:46.000 --> 46:53.000
St George is the patron saint of England, and today is England's national day.

46:53.000 --> 46:55.000
Can you see all the flags?

46:55.000 --> 46:58.000
The flags with a red cross on a white background?

46:58.000 --> 47:01.000
Yes, that's the flag of England.

47:01.000 --> 47:08.000
And some people are wearing a red rose, because the rose is our national flower.

47:08.000 --> 47:11.000
But what are all the people waiting for?

47:11.000 --> 47:16.000
They are waiting to see the mayor release red and white balloons.

47:16.000 --> 47:19.000
Then there is a children's costume competition.

47:19.000 --> 47:24.000
And in a minute, you can see George kill the dragon.

47:24.000 --> 47:26.000
How exciting!

47:26.000 --> 47:28.000
Can you see that soldier?

47:28.000 --> 47:30.000
The one on the horse?

47:30.000 --> 47:32.000
Yes, he is George.

47:32.000 --> 47:37.000
And over there near the cave is the princess.

47:37.000 --> 47:40.000
Can you see the girl with long blonde hair?

47:40.000 --> 47:43.000
She is wearing a long dress.

47:43.000 --> 47:44.000
Oh yes.

47:44.000 --> 47:47.000
And look, there is the dragon.

47:47.000 --> 47:49.000
Quick, let's move closer.

47:49.000 --> 47:54.000
The show is starting.

47:54.000 --> 47:56.000
Chapter 10.

47:56.000 --> 47:58.000
The prize.

47:58.000 --> 48:03.000
It is morning, and the weather is perfect.

48:03.000 --> 48:12.000
Bathsheba watches Mr Potts the postman take a letter in a gold envelope to Captain Troy's house.

48:12.000 --> 48:18.000
Captain Troy opens the letter and goes into his front garden.

48:18.000 --> 48:22.000
Bathsheba wants to see Captain Troy again.

48:22.000 --> 48:25.000
She walks past his house.

48:25.000 --> 48:28.000
Hello Bathsheba.

48:28.000 --> 48:30.000
How lovely to see you again.

48:30.000 --> 48:33.000
Captain Troy says.

48:33.000 --> 48:35.000
Do you remember me?

48:35.000 --> 48:37.000
Bathsheba smiles.

48:37.000 --> 48:40.000
I do, she says.

48:40.000 --> 48:43.000
I've got a gold letter too.

48:43.000 --> 48:47.000
It's a letter from Miracle Supermarket.

48:47.000 --> 48:50.000
There's a prize for their special customers.

48:50.000 --> 48:53.000
And she takes it from her bag.

48:53.000 --> 48:57.000
Miracle Supermarket first prize.

48:57.000 --> 49:01.000
A day at five-star Glencrag Castle.

49:01.000 --> 49:05.000
Travel by dragon with free dragon parking.

49:05.000 --> 49:08.000
Dancing in the dragon disco.

49:08.000 --> 49:10.000
Friday morning, 9am.

49:10.000 --> 49:13.000
Captain Troy laughs.

49:13.000 --> 49:15.000
It can't be true.

49:15.000 --> 49:17.000
I don't believe it.

49:17.000 --> 49:21.000
We all know that there are only dragons in stories.

49:21.000 --> 49:25.000
There aren't any dragons in Sunnyville.

49:25.000 --> 49:33.000
Just then, they hear a strange sound and a large green dragon comes through a cloud in the sky.

49:33.000 --> 49:37.000
Gulliver lands on the grass next to them.

49:37.000 --> 49:38.000
Wow.

49:38.000 --> 49:40.000
Says Captain Troy.

49:40.000 --> 49:42.000
I can't believe it.

49:42.000 --> 49:44.000
There really are dragons.

49:45.000 --> 49:47.000
Of course there are.

49:47.000 --> 49:48.000
Says Gulliver.

49:48.000 --> 49:52.000
Climb up and fasten your seatbelt.

49:52.000 --> 49:55.000
But what about Bathsheba?

49:55.000 --> 49:57.000
Captain Troy asks.

49:57.000 --> 49:59.000
She's got a letter too.

49:59.000 --> 50:02.000
Sophia is taking her.

50:02.000 --> 50:04.000
Gulliver replies.

50:04.000 --> 50:06.000
Who's Sophia?

50:06.000 --> 50:08.000
Bathsheba asks.

50:08.000 --> 50:11.000
You hear him!

50:11.000 --> 50:13.000
Says a voice in the sky.

50:13.000 --> 50:17.000
Something large flies over the trees.

50:17.000 --> 50:19.000
It is another dragon.

50:19.000 --> 50:23.000
Her silver scales shine in the sunshine.

50:23.000 --> 50:31.000
She is a small dragon, but her unusual color and purple eyes make her very beautiful.

50:31.000 --> 50:34.000
Who says there aren't any dragons?

50:34.000 --> 50:36.000
Sophia says.

50:36.000 --> 50:39.000
Bathsheba climbs up onto her neck.

50:39.000 --> 50:41.000
Time to go!

50:42.000 --> 50:44.000
Says Gulliver.

50:44.000 --> 50:52.000
The dragons touch noses and Captain Troy smiles at Bathsheba before they fly up over the

50:52.000 --> 50:56.000
dark woods and through the clouds.

50:56.000 --> 51:03.000
Glen Crag Castle stands on the top of a crystal mountain next to a glass lake.

51:03.000 --> 51:05.000
It is wonderful.

51:05.000 --> 51:11.000
Bathsheba and Captain Troy sit and talk in the beautiful dining room.

51:11.000 --> 51:15.000
They go for walks in the castle gardens.

51:15.000 --> 51:17.000
They play golf.

51:17.000 --> 51:23.000
And before dinner, they race on their dragons through the blue mountains.

51:23.000 --> 51:26.000
The wizard is right.

51:26.000 --> 51:31.000
Bathsheba and Captain Troy don't need the love potion.

51:32.000 --> 51:40.000
When Gulliver and the beautiful Sophia take them home on Friday evening, they are in love.

51:40.000 --> 51:48.000
The only problem now is that Captain Troy can't tell people about the dragons and the castle.

51:48.000 --> 51:54.000
Bathsheba makes a spell and blows it into his house.

51:54.000 --> 51:56.000
It's all a dream.

51:56.000 --> 51:58.000
It isn't real.

51:58.000 --> 52:01.000
A dream of dragons and of meals.

52:01.000 --> 52:04.000
In a castle in the sky.

52:04.000 --> 52:07.000
Playing golf on mountains high.

52:07.000 --> 52:09.000
I feel ill.

52:09.000 --> 52:14.000
I've got a fever and I can't ever forget.

52:14.000 --> 52:16.000
Bathsheba!

52:16.000 --> 52:22.000
The dragons and the day at Glen Crag Castle become a wonderful dream.

52:22.000 --> 52:26.000
But there is a girl he can't forget.

52:26.000 --> 52:33.000
Bathsheba and Captain Troy meet in the village and have cups of hot chocolate in the cafe.

52:33.000 --> 52:38.000
They go walking in the park and dancing in the evening.

52:38.000 --> 52:43.000
Bathsheba has got a boyfriend at last.

52:43.000 --> 52:51.000
She has also got two new dragon friends and she lives happily and peacefully.

52:51.000 --> 52:55.000
Until the next adventure.

52:58.000 --> 53:01.000
Listening activity.

53:01.000 --> 53:05.000
So, what post have we got this morning?

53:05.000 --> 53:11.000
The first letter in the pink envelope is for Mrs Evans.

53:11.000 --> 53:15.000
She lives at number 22 Beach Lane.

53:15.000 --> 53:24.000
This is spelt B E E C H and the number is 22.

53:24.000 --> 53:28.000
The green envelope is for Miss Sims.

53:28.000 --> 53:32.000
She lives at a house called Hedgeside.

53:32.000 --> 53:41.000
That's spelt H E D G E S I D E.

53:41.000 --> 53:45.000
It's number 14 The High Street.

53:45.000 --> 53:49.000
The yellow envelope is Mr Sharp's letter.

53:49.000 --> 53:55.000
Mr Sharp lives at Rose Cottage and that's in Linden Lane.

53:55.000 --> 54:01.000
Spelt L Y N D O N.

54:01.000 --> 54:10.000
The brown envelope is for Mrs Gates and she lives at 13 Chester Drive.

54:10.000 --> 54:19.000
That's 13 C H E S T E R Drive.

54:19.000 --> 54:26.000
Her postcode is S U 2 4 L D.

54:26.000 --> 54:30.000
Thank you for your help.

